Two boys who went missing on Saturday in Pienaaspoort in Mamelodi east of Pretoria have been found dead. The two boys were reported missing last Saturday. Their parents have said the boys were playing in the streets when they vanished. The police diving unit discovered the bodies in a stream at Pienaarspoort, east of Mamelodi. Their families have been left distraught upon the discovery, as they were still hopeful that maybe the boys would come back still alive. The search and rescue unit and the diving unit of the SAPS discovered the bodies nearby a stream. Forensic teams are still trying to assess and retrace the last steps of the two teenagers. 